e Guide</h1><div class=3D"single-post-content__inner"><div class=3D"bialty-=
container"><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">You=E2=80=99ve posed for th=
e shot. You=E2=80=99ve taken the picture. You might have even added that In=
stagram filter to spice it up a little bit. It=E2=80=99s a fantastic pictur=
e and you want to get it printed off and framed =E2=80=93 and that=E2=80=99=
s where the difficulty starts. What size frame? What style frame? Should I =
have the photo backed? All reasonable questions have reasonable answers if =
you take the time to explore them.</span></p><h3>Most Popular Picture Frame=
 Sizes&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Choosing the pe=
rfect picture frame size is easier than you probably think, especially sinc=
e there are so many different photo sizes to choose from. Most popular size=
s include 5=C3=977 and 8=C3=9710, but both can be adapted to accommodate al=
ternative sized photos, with some careful design backing</span><b>.</b></p>=
<figure class=3D"wp-block-table is-style-stripes"><table class=3D"has-fixed=
-layout"><tbody><tr><td><strong>Imperial (inches)</strong></td><td><strong>=
Metric (cm)</strong></td></tr><tr><td>4 x 6</td><td>10 x 15</td></tr><tr><t=
